m/psx/bof4/art13/drag-11.jpg height=80width=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Need an idea for animation</span><hr size=1> We've got a competition coming up and the deadline is in Sept. ...<br>
Basically we're required to hand in an animation vid <br>
(5 mins long, theme of our choice...)<br>
I'm doing an anime piece but there's one thing:<br>
<br>
I can't think of a short story that will require less voice actors/sfxs (as I'm an amature) and yet be so impressive... the competiotion is international... so I need an idea that will REALLY impress the judges<br>
<br>
THank you all for your time... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ualucard1515.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alucard1515</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/30/01 8:16:27 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need an idea for animation</span><hr size=1> You're required to do 5 minutes of animation? Ouch, seems like a lot for one person. Hmm, I have a tough time coming up with stories off the top of my head, but you definitely need to keep it simple. Sorry that I'm not very helpful. <p><embed src="http://www.undeadart.com/temp/flashsig.swf"  width="180" height="60">
<br>
Thomas Bonvillain<br>
<a href=http://www.undeadart.com>undeadart.com</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uashjaded.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ash Jaded </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/30/01 10:50:12 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thegia.com/psx/bof4/art13/drag-11.jpg height=80width=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need an idea for animation</span><hr size=1> yeah well, I would probably tend to trick the audience as anime animators do... <br>
Keep most of the shots were only the mouth moves, etc...<br>
also if I don't have much time I could end up with an SD music vid... or something like that... <br>
<br>
[edit] I reaally need to get myself a light desk... trying to animate on a clip board makes your limbs cramp and your eyes ach... not healthy...<br>
<br>
Anyone got any tips for the amature animator here...?<br>
I'd reallly appreciate it... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uashjaded.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ash Jaded </A> at: 4/30/01 10:54:04 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udarkora.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/30/01 2:06:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need an idea for animation</span><hr size=1>   Well, you could do a battle scene from the perspective of a bystander...a long, drawn out battle in the city causing all kinds of property damage.  You get to watch the bystander move away from the battle, but peek back curiously here and there...lots of dodging of rubble and stray shots.  Then when the two combatants have simultaneously defeated each other and are laying there amidst the rubble, you could shift the perspective from the bystander to an overview of everything, including the bystander.  Now to make it even more interesting, have the bystander be a little kitten or a puppy or such and show them as being completely unscathed with everything around them in ruins.  I personally haven't seen it done anywhere in an animation realm, but I'm sure it's been done in books or comics and such (I don't remember exactly where, but I'm sure I've read something similar before)...but with the main perspective as an animal, you don't really have to voice any thoughts--just lots of visuals and background sounds.  HTH  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ueaglemaina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EagleMaina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/30/01 6:29:28 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://pages.infinit.net/maina2/ezboard/maina.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need an idea for animation</span><hr size=1> Not that I want to discourage you, but 5 min for Sept?????<br>
<br>
It's almost impossible!!! I will have around 1 min of film to do next year (colored and with sound) and I have a full year to do this. If you really want quality you cannot do tons of animation.(almost none from my point of view)<br>
Few camera movements. Not lots of backgrounds either, or none.<br>
 <br>
I really mean this. Even my teachers (and they are professionnals ) can only do around 1 min of film in a summer (e.i. in 2-3 months) If you are not familiar with the process, it's gonna be even tougher. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://pages.infinit.net/maina"><img src="http://pages.infinit.net/maina/images/banner01.jpg" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uashjaded.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ash Jaded </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/1/01 4:23:21 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thegia.com/psx/bof4/art13/drag-11.jpg height=80width=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need an idea for animation</span><hr size=1> I guess what  they're looking for is 3D animation or Web-animation... I don't think I'll be up for 3D animation...<br>
<br>
I could do a few seconds of clips here and there... and the rest would be Special FX or somethin...<br>
<br>
I myself don't think I'll manage since I'm travelling in the summer and won't have access to any software... <br>
<br>
Wouldn't hurt to try though... even if I don't meet the deadline,<br>
this motivates me to try something new...<br>
anyways... When I start with something (even a few secs long) you guys would see it  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uironfistking.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IronfistKing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fresh Meat</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/1/01 4:10:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need an idea for animation</span><hr size=1> I have a story: a few killer robots meet up with killer gnomes and have a fight for 2 years until talking pies come out of the sky to kill everyone. That, or a guy making a castle out of tooth picks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showMessage?topicID=1204.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showMessage?topicID=1203.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=1198.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.threadControl?topicID=1198.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1198.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1198.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="ri